
mmap_dd is a small dd-like utility for copying data to and from
mmapable files. This is usefull for the resource files that map to
PCIE BAR spaces in the sysfs hierarchy which cannot be read or written
to otherwise. It's also handy to test and benchmark mmap style drivers
(ie mtramon).

To build, run:

  ./waf

To install, run:

  ./waf install
